A RESOLUTION
1 Recognizing the Lunar New Year Celebration; and for other purposes.
2 WHEREAS, January 29, 2025, marks the beginning of the Lunar New Year, which is
3 celebrated in many Asian communities around the world, including the United States and
4 especially in Georgia; and
5 WHEREAS, Georgia is home to nearly 500,000 Asian and Pacific Islander Americans of
6 Bangladeshi, Cambodian, Chinese, Filipino, Hmong, Indian, Indonesian, Iu-Mien, Japanese,
7 Korean, Laotian, Malaysian, Pakistani, Sri Lankan, Taiwanese, and Vietnamese descent,
8 which is approximately 4 percent of Georgia's total population; and
9 WHEREAS, the Asian and Pacific Islander American community has contributed to the
10 social, cultural, civic, economic, and academic success of the State of Georgia; and
11 WHEREAS, the Lunar New Year is predominately celebrated by Chinese, Korean, and
12 Vietnamese residents of Georgia, who account for approximately 200,000 Georgians; and
